    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-01-31T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-01-31T20:00:00-05:00" n="324"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d324">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">693.001/504: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Hankow</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Josselyn</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hankow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-02-01T09:00:00+08:00"
                            >February 1, 1939—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received February 2—5 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Shanghai’s January 31, 6 p.m.,<note n="78" xml:id="d324fn78">Not printed.</note>
                    and Tokyo’s January 31, noon, return of Americans to Hankow. The party of
                    foreigners mentioned in Shanghai’s 59, January 20, 3 [<hi rend="italic">5</hi>]
                    p.m. to the Department arrived at Hankow on board the <hi rend="italic">Shinyo
                        Maru</hi> January 30th. According to Father Ralph Reilly of Franciscan
                    Fathers of New York, there were 36 foreign passengers and Reilly was only
                    American citizen on board.</p>
                <p>British Vice Consul McDermott arrived here from Shanghai last week on a Japanese
                    naval transport plane which was half empty.</p>
                <p>Sent to Shanghai and Peiping. Shanghai please repeat to Tokyo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Josselyn</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
